name: Go Export Data
summary: Learn about .GOX files and view a list of programs that open them.

windows.name: Open over 400 file formats with File Viewer Plus.Free Download

content: Gccgo is part of the GNU Compiler Collection (GCC). Developers use gccgo to compile and build Go programs.

When a developer uses gccgo to compile a file that exports functions, they can choose to store a description of those exported functions in a GOX file. This file functions similarly to a C or C++ .H file. When a developer uses gccgo to compile a file that imports the exported functions, gccgo searches for an accompanying GOX file (or SO, A, or O file, if a GOX file isn't found) and uses it to import the functions correctly.

description: A GOX file is an export data file created by gccgo, a compiler for the Go programming language. It contains a description of functions exported from a compiled .O file. Developers produce GOX files using the objcopy -j .go_export command.

instructions: GOX files are not meant to be opened. You can use GOX files to import functions while compiling programs with gccgo (multiplatform).
